I can't believe...

262
00:09:07,073 --> 00:09:08,502
- Right. - that it has been seven years.

263
00:09:08,503 --> 00:09:10,319
(It's hard to believe that it has been 7 years.)

264
00:09:10,343 --> 00:09:13,242
Seriously, it's hard for us to gather around.

265
00:09:13,243 --> 00:09:15,319
But we managed to do that for the first time in a while.

266
00:09:15,343 --> 00:09:18,482
I hope we'll do more things together from now on.

267
00:09:18,483 --> 00:09:19,483
I know.

268
00:09:19,484 --> 00:09:20,882
Everyone will be busy, but still.

269
00:09:20,883 --> 00:09:23,722
I hope we'll meet regularly after this show.

270
00:09:23,723 --> 00:09:26,469
(Careful not to pressure each other, they timidly share their sincerity.)

271
00:09:26,493 --> 00:09:29,392
It'll be nice to take the stage.

272
00:09:29,393 --> 00:09:32,092
I told you that I wanted to see you wearing smoky makeup.

273
00:09:32,093 --> 00:09:35,933
Our fans, Wannable, are hopeful for a performance,

274
00:09:36,263 --> 00:09:38,532
but they aren't certain.

275
00:09:38,533 --> 00:09:40,632
- I know. - They don't want to be let down.

276
00:09:40,633 --> 00:09:42,873
KCON LA.

277
00:09:43,173 --> 00:09:46,012
After Wanna One came to be,

278
00:09:46,013 --> 00:09:48,183
we went there before our debut album got released.

279
00:09:49,683 --> 00:09:55,483
(They took the stage as Wanna One for the 1st time at 2017 KCON LA.)

280
00:09:55,853 --> 00:09:59,153
It'll be memorable for Wannable if we attend the event again.

281
00:09:59,493 --> 00:10:00,993
It'll be so meaningful.

282
00:10:02,323 --> 00:10:03,523
I really want to go there.

283
00:10:05,393 --> 00:10:08,703
(For Wannable, they want to do more things as Wanna One.)

284
00:10:09,763 --> 00:10:16,173
(Now they've met, all of them want a new beginning.)

285
00:10:17,873 --> 00:10:20,242
(Glancing around)

286
00:10:20,243 --> 00:10:21,243
Hey, so...

287
00:10:22,143 --> 00:10:24,152
We had planned to drink today,

288
00:10:24,153 --> 00:10:27,653
so I brought a nice liquor.

289
00:10:28,553 --> 00:10:30,473
You've said that many times. What did you bring?

290
00:10:30,583 --> 00:10:32,522
That's right. You promised to bring it out.

291
00:10:32,523 --> 00:10:33,822
Can I bring it out now?

292
00:10:33,823 --> 00:10:35,393
- Sure. Let's drink it. - Of course.

293
00:10:35,823 --> 00:10:36,993
I'll bring it out.

294
00:10:37,363 --> 00:10:38,892
Just how nice is it?

295
00:10:38,893 --> 00:10:40,902
I know. He began talking about it five hours ago.

296
00:10:40,903 --> 00:10:43,533
No, he began talking about it the moment we hit the road.

297
00:10:45,003 --> 00:10:46,643
(He hid the nice liquor inside the tent.)

298
00:10:46,773 --> 00:10:49,013
- What? Is it Kaoliang liquor? - Is it a Chinese liquor?

299
00:10:49,173 --> 00:10:51,373
I haven't seen this bright face of him like this today.

300
00:10:51,443 --> 00:10:53,942
In China, this liquor is the most well-known...

301
00:10:53,943 --> 00:10:55,863
- and the most expensive. - What? Could it be...

302
00:10:56,243 --> 00:10:57,643
- Gosh, what's that? - My goodness.

303
00:10:58,413 --> 00:10:59,482
(Sung Woon brought the high-end Chinese Kaoliang liquor.)

304
00:10:59,483 --> 00:11:00,483
What's that?

305
00:11:00,484 --> 00:11:01,629
(Sung Woon brought the high-end Chinese Kaoliang liquor.)

306
00:11:01,653 --> 00:11:02,982
- Is that a nice liquor? - What's this?

307
00:11:02,983 --> 00:11:05,453
- Apparently, it's very expensive. - Is it expensive?

308
00:11:05,723 --> 00:11:06,899
Sung Woon, where did you get it?

309
00:11:06,923 --> 00:11:08,023
Actually, this liquor is...

310
00:11:09,093 --> 00:11:10,822
- from Kuan Lin. - What?

311
00:11:10,823 --> 00:11:12,362
(Actually, this liquor is from Kuan Lin.)

312
00:11:12,363 --> 00:11:13,792
He gifted it...

313
00:11:13,793 --> 00:11:15,763
so that the members could drink together.

314
00:11:16,033 --> 00:11:17,162
Really?

315
00:11:17,163 --> 00:11:18,172
Gosh, Kuan Lin. Thank you.

316
00:11:18,173 --> 00:11:19,632
- He wanted us to drink together. - Seriously.

317
00:11:19,633 --> 00:11:20,633
Really?

318
00:11:20,634 --> 00:11:23,103
(Congratulations on teaming up again.)

319
00:11:23,373 --> 00:11:24,712
Let's have a glass each.

320
00:11:24,713 --> 00:11:25,713
That's a good idea.

321
00:11:26,413 --> 00:11:29,542
(They decide to have a glass each while thinking about Kuan Lin.)

322
00:11:29,543 --> 00:11:31,683
What? Seong Wu!

323
00:11:32,083 --> 00:11:33,483
(What's that noise?)

324
00:11:33,813 --> 00:11:35,082
(That's Kuan Lin's voice.)

325
00:11:35,083 --> 00:11:37,322
- What? - Sung Woon!

326
00:11:37,323 --> 00:11:38,822
- What? - Jae Hwan!

327
00:11:38,823 --> 00:11:40,123
- Hey! - Seong Wu.

328
00:11:40,653 --> 00:11:41,663
Min Hyun.

329
00:11:41,763 --> 00:11:43,323
- Hey. - What's going on?

330
00:11:43,423 --> 00:11:44,532
- What? - What?

331
00:11:44,533 --> 00:11:46,032
- What's this? - Kuan Lin.

332
00:11:46,033 --> 00:11:47,662
What? It's a video message.

333
00:11:47,663 --> 00:11:49,703
(A letter on the screen?)

334
00:11:49,903 --> 00:11:51,272
Are you serious? I got goosebumps.

335
00:11:51,273 --> 00:11:52,273
I got goosebumps.

336
00:11:52,703 --> 00:11:54,073
I miss Kuan Lin.

337
00:11:55,303 --> 00:11:56,542
It has begun.

338
00:11:56,543 --> 00:11:58,173
(To Wanna One members)

339
00:11:58,273 --> 00:11:59,913
- What's this? - What?

340
00:12:00,673 --> 00:12:03,742
(To Wanna One members)

341
00:12:03,743 --> 00:12:06,012
Members, it has been a while.

342
00:12:06,013 --> 00:12:07,559
(They haven't heard from Kuan Lin in a while.)

343
00:12:07,583 --> 00:12:09,322
- Gosh, I'm tearing up. - Same here.

344
00:12:09,323 --> 00:12:11,292
- Hearing his voice makes me sad. - I know.

345
00:12:11,293 --> 00:12:12,923
- Same here. - Same here.

346
00:12:12,993 --> 00:12:16,022
(They calm their hearts and focus on the video message.)

347
00:12:16,023 --> 00:12:18,793
(B-side: A few days before the first meeting)

348
00:12:18,933 --> 00:12:20,463
- Hello. - Hello.

349
00:12:21,633 --> 00:12:22,633
It's Sung Woon.

350
00:12:22,933 --> 00:12:24,203
Why am I on the screen?

351
00:12:24,673 --> 00:12:26,332
(Why is Sung Woon on the screen?)

352
00:12:26,333 --> 00:12:28,973
How did it feel to watch the teaser?

353
00:12:30,043 --> 00:12:31,842
Many people are waiting for Kuan Lin.

354
00:12:31,843 --> 00:12:33,012
I got that from the comments.

355
00:12:33,013 --> 00:12:34,359
They were like, "How about Kuan Lin?"

356
00:12:34,383 --> 00:12:36,813
They don't think Kuan Lin will come.

357
00:12:37,143 --> 00:12:38,453
It'll be nice if he comes.

358
00:12:39,383 --> 00:12:41,083
Shall I look into his address?

359
00:12:42,823 --> 00:12:44,423
I want to know how he is doing.

360
00:12:45,493 --> 00:12:46,893
I haven't seen him in a long while.

361
00:12:47,993 --> 00:12:48,993
(A few days later)

362
00:12:48,994 --> 00:12:50,092
(Sung Woon: Director! I got in touch with Kuan Lin!)

363
00:12:50,093 --> 00:12:51,162
(The production crew got messages from Sung Woon.)

364
00:12:51,163 --> 00:12:52,163
(Really?)

365
00:12:52,193 --> 00:12:53,292
(Sung Woon: Kuan Lin said he'd greet us...)

366
00:12:53,293 --> 00:12:54,662
(if we visited Beijing.)

367
00:12:54,663 --> 00:12:55,932
(That's great.)

368
00:12:55,933 --> 00:12:57,702
(Let's go and meet Kuan Lin together!)

369
00:12:57,703 --> 00:12:59,372
(Sung Woon: Sounds good!)

370
00:12:59,373 --> 00:13:02,503
(Thus began the project.)

371
00:13:04,513 --> 00:13:05,872
(In Search of Kuan Lin with Sung Woon)

372
00:13:05,873 --> 00:13:07,413
- Did you actually go there? - What?

373
00:13:08,383 --> 00:13:09,383
Did you go there?

374
00:13:09,384 --> 00:13:10,589
(Did you film the reunion too?)

375
00:13:10,613 --> 00:13:11,952
(Will we watch the reunion now?)

376
00:13:11,953 --> 00:13:14,082
This is incredible.

377
00:13:14,083 --> 00:13:16,182
Why am I on the screen, not Kuan Lin?

378
00:13:16,183 --> 00:13:17,382
For goodness' sake.

379
00:13:17,383 --> 00:13:18,943
(He feels embarrassed for some reason.)

380
00:13:19,353 --> 00:13:20,353
Beijing.

381
00:13:20,354 --> 00:13:21,662
(He booked a flight right away to see Kuan Lin.)

382
00:13:21,663 --> 00:13:23,263
For real?

383
00:13:23,923 --> 00:13:26,993
(Sung Woon flew to Beijing at once.)

384
00:13:27,293 --> 00:13:30,363
(Half excited, half worried)

385
00:13:30,603 --> 00:13:33,833
(A bit later)

386
00:13:33,973 --> 00:13:35,173
(He lands in Beijing.)

387
00:13:36,473 --> 00:13:38,673
(Nervous and excited)

388
00:13:39,573 --> 00:13:40,973
My goodness.

389
00:13:42,743 --> 00:13:44,183
I'm a bit nervous.

390
00:13:46,053 --> 00:13:47,053
I'm a bit nervous.

391
00:13:47,313 --> 00:13:49,252
Why am I nervous? I mean...

392
00:13:49,253 --> 00:13:50,813
(They'll be reunited after many years.)

393
00:13:50,853 --> 00:13:51,853
It feels...

394
00:13:52,793 --> 00:13:55,162
It feels strange.

395
00:13:55,163 --> 00:13:56,469
(He can't describe this feeling.)

396
00:13:56,493 --> 00:13:59,533
You know, I can feel your sincerity.

397
00:14:00,593 --> 00:14:02,462
We were meeting again after many years.

398
00:14:02,463 --> 00:14:04,103
It had been nearly ten years.

399
00:14:05,133 --> 00:14:06,702
None of us has seen Kuan Lin.

400
00:14:06,703 --> 00:14:08,943
(The members haven't seen Kuan Lin after he left Korea.)

401
00:14:09,003 --> 00:14:11,002
(Sung Woon steps outside the airport.)

402
00:14:11,003 --> 00:14:12,412
I would've been nervous too.

403
00:14:12,413 --> 00:14:13,572
I'm nervous right now.

404
00:14:13,573 --> 00:14:15,082
Watching this makes me nervous.

405
00:14:15,083 --> 00:14:16,589
(How will Kuan Lin look after 7 years?)

406
00:14:16,613 --> 00:14:18,783
(Looking around)

407
00:14:22,083 --> 00:14:23,253
Kuan Lin!

408
00:14:25,293 --> 00:14:27,762
- Is it Kuan Lin? - They met!

409
00:14:27,763 --> 00:14:29,662
- Are you serious? - No way!

410
00:14:29,663 --> 00:14:31,732
(It's 10 seconds before meeting Kuan Lin.)

411
00:14:31,733 --> 00:14:33,093
(The members get nervous as well.)

412
00:14:34,503 --> 00:14:35,663
Kuan Lin!

413
00:14:54,553 --> 00:14:55,753
Kuan Lin!

414
00:14:56,323 --> 00:14:58,993
(Lai Kuan Lin shows himself after many years.)

415
00:14:59,153 --> 00:15:05,493
(They finally see Kuan Lin.)

416
00:15:11,873 --> 00:15:12,933
Kuan Lin!

417
00:15:13,803 --> 00:15:14,943
Kuan Lin!

418
00:15:16,273 --> 00:15:18,173
- My goodness. - It's Kuan Lin.

419
00:15:18,513 --> 00:15:20,573
He looks more dependable now.

420
00:15:20,773 --> 00:15:22,343
(Proud and happy to see him)

421
00:15:24,183 --> 00:15:26,423
(The youngest member came to the airport for Sung Woon.)

422
00:15:26,513 --> 00:15:28,482
(Sung Woon, welcome.)

423
00:15:28,483 --> 00:15:29,883
He still has long arms.

424
00:15:30,283 --> 00:15:32,493
- Kuan Lin! - He has become cooler.

425
00:15:34,463 --> 00:15:35,593
Hey, bro.

426
00:15:35,663 --> 00:15:36,863
- Yo. - Hey.

427
00:15:37,763 --> 00:15:38,933
- Yo. - Hey.

428
00:15:39,333 --> 00:15:40,432
- What's this? - Have you been well?

429
00:15:40,433 --> 00:15:41,502
Yes, Sung Woon.

430
00:15:41,503 --> 00:15:43,783
(Having missed each other, they greet each other warmly.)

431
00:15:44,263 --> 00:15:45,433
He hasn't changed.

432
00:15:48,403 --> 00:15:54,583
(They can't take their eyes off since they've missed Kuan Lin.)

433
00:15:58,683 --> 00:16:01,553
I mean, it has been a while.

434
00:16:01,853 --> 00:16:03,623
- How nice. - My goodness.

435
00:16:05,453 --> 00:16:06,793
He is still handsome.

436
00:16:08,523 --> 00:16:10,492
- Thanks for coming. - Kuan Lin.

437
00:16:10,493 --> 00:16:11,633
Yes, Sung Woon?

438
00:16:12,393 --> 00:16:16,063
(They go to the restaurant Kuan Lin has reserved for Sung Woon.)

439
00:16:16,233 --> 00:16:17,332
(Happy)

440
00:16:17,333 --> 00:16:19,273
(Seeing Sung Woon puts him in a great mood.)

441
00:16:20,773 --> 00:16:24,073
(Sung Woon saves Kuan Lin's face in his phone.)

442
00:16:24,673 --> 00:16:25,943
Sung Woon, eat some mushrooms.

443
00:16:26,643 --> 00:16:28,243
Won't the broth get on your sleeve?

444
00:16:28,313 --> 00:16:29,642
(Considerate and sweet)

445
00:16:29,643 --> 00:16:32,113
- I didn't know Sung Woon was... - He looks after Kuan Lin.

446
00:16:32,553 --> 00:16:34,152
So affectionate.

447
00:16:34,153 --> 00:16:35,283
(Surprised)

448
00:16:35,523 --> 00:16:37,452
He loves Korean food so much...

449
00:16:37,453 --> 00:16:39,422
that he cooks it himself. He cooks everything.

450
00:16:39,423 --> 00:16:40,553
That's right.

451
00:16:40,653 --> 00:16:41,922
- When I first moved to Beijing, - Really?

452
00:16:41,923 --> 00:16:42,962
I didn't have many friends.

453
00:16:42,963 --> 00:16:45,262
- I didn't have my family here. - It's understandable.

454
00:16:45,263 --> 00:16:47,632
- I wanted to find Korean food, - Because he lived in Korea...

455
00:16:47,633 --> 00:16:49,663
but I didn't have anyone to ask.

456
00:16:50,063 --> 00:16:53,533
So I had no choice but to cook...

457
00:16:54,233 --> 00:16:56,443
in order to eat tasty Korean food.

458
00:16:57,843 --> 00:17:00,013
- In order to eat tasty Korean food. - Gosh.

459
00:17:00,173 --> 00:17:01,682
- So... - I feel bad.

460
00:17:01,683 --> 00:17:03,942
I can make bossam, braised hairtail,

461
00:17:03,943 --> 00:17:07,252
and other dishes using mackerel.

462
00:17:07,253 --> 00:17:09,253
Are you working on a script?

463
00:17:09,683 --> 00:17:14,252
I joined a film production company in China.

464
00:17:14,253 --> 00:17:15,993
While working in the company,

465
00:17:16,193 --> 00:17:19,792
I'm learning about scripts.

466
00:17:19,793 --> 00:17:24,003
I mostly work on short films.

467
00:17:24,463 --> 00:17:26,973
I get my monthly salary.

468
00:17:27,233 --> 00:17:30,143
It makes me feel secure.

469
00:17:30,803 --> 00:17:33,143
(Kuan Lin is all grown up.)

470
00:17:33,713 --> 00:17:35,513
He has become very mature.

471
00:17:36,513 --> 00:17:38,113
- He grew up a lot. - Seriously.

472
00:17:40,283 --> 00:17:41,482
How are things now?

473
00:17:41,483 --> 00:17:43,622
- Things are great now. - Are you looking after yourself?

474
00:17:43,623 --> 00:17:45,892
- Yes. Things are great now. - I'm so glad to hear that.

475
00:17:45,893 --> 00:17:50,823
I love that I'm advancing slowly.

476
00:17:51,193 --> 00:17:56,332
It's different from becoming a singer very quickly.

477
00:17:56,333 --> 00:17:59,273
I'm putting in the effort...

478
00:18:00,003 --> 00:18:04,843
and advancing slowly, and I love myself for it.

479
00:18:06,943 --> 00:18:10,513
(He debuted right after a short period of training.)

480
00:18:11,043 --> 00:18:15,123
(Living as an idol was a bit too much for Kuan Lin.)

481
00:18:16,483 --> 00:18:17,683
He is cool.

482
00:18:18,953 --> 00:18:20,022
He is so cool.

483
00:18:20,023 --> 00:18:22,362
(Now, he works for his new dream at his own speed.)

484
00:18:22,363 --> 00:18:24,632
(Video courtesy of Lai Kuan Lin's account on Weibo)

485
00:18:24,633 --> 00:18:28,332
(Kuan Lin is happy about his slow, but sturdy growth.)

486
00:18:28,333 --> 00:18:32,033
(Kuan Lin is happy about his slow, but sturdy growth.)

487
00:18:33,573 --> 00:18:35,303
How are you good at Korean?

488
00:18:36,643 --> 00:18:37,672
Your Korean has improved...

489
00:18:37,673 --> 00:18:38,742
- since your Wanna One days. - I know.

490
00:18:38,743 --> 00:18:41,613
It's because I still miss Korea.

491
00:18:42,943 --> 00:18:46,453
(Although he has left years ago, he still misses Korea.)

492
00:18:49,983 --> 00:18:51,393
It has been many years.

493
00:18:54,493 --> 00:18:55,733
You should come back, Kuan Lin.

494
00:18:58,193 --> 00:18:59,232
What's that?

495
00:18:59,233 --> 00:19:00,869
(Kuan Lin shows Sung Woon a tattoo on his arm.)

496
00:19:00,893 --> 00:19:02,033
This is August 7.

497
00:19:03,533 --> 00:19:06,972
(August 7?)

498
00:19:06,973 --> 00:19:08,142
- It's Wanna One's... - That's right.

499
00:19:08,143 --> 00:19:09,673
- Wanna One's debut date. - No way!

500
00:19:11,273 --> 00:19:13,072
Did he get a tattoo of the debut date?

501
00:19:13,073 --> 00:19:14,882
(Kuan Lin tattooed a memory of their time together...)

502
00:19:14,883 --> 00:19:16,712
(during the years they haven't seen each other.)

503
00:19:16,713 --> 00:19:17,843
That's incredible.

504
00:19:19,413 --> 00:19:22,923
If anyone were to ask me when I'd like to be congratulated...

505
00:19:23,253 --> 00:19:25,252
or when...

506
00:19:25,253 --> 00:19:28,762
I'd personally like to commemorate,

507
00:19:28,763 --> 00:19:31,323
I'd say that it's August 7.

508
00:19:33,933 --> 00:19:37,962
It was the day our effort came back as a good result.

509
00:19:37,963 --> 00:19:40,243
(They worked together and bore fruit that was Wanna One.)

510
00:19:40,573 --> 00:19:41,973
I'm tearing up.

511
00:19:42,003 --> 00:19:43,173
Seriously.

512
00:19:45,973 --> 00:19:51,182
(The youngest one might've missed Wanna One...)

513
00:19:51,183 --> 00:19:54,953
(more than anyone.)

514
00:19:57,223 --> 00:19:59,593
(Wanna One's video message to Kuan Lin)

515
00:19:59,923 --> 00:20:02,623
(Embarrassed and shy)

516
00:20:02,763 --> 00:20:03,963
I'll turn it on.

517
00:20:04,393 --> 00:20:05,662
Can you hear the sound?

518
00:20:05,663 --> 00:20:06,892
I can hear it.

519
00:20:06,893 --> 00:20:08,813
(Feeling nervous, he watches the video message.)

520
00:20:09,903 --> 00:20:11,832
The member I haven't seen in the longest time?

521
00:20:11,833 --> 00:20:14,113
(Who is the member you haven't seen in the longest time?)

522
00:20:14,173 --> 00:20:15,943
Well, it's Kuan Lin.

523
